headline: Here’s the Supporting Cast Potentially Helping Intel in Its Turnaround

Intel has approached Apple and Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing about investments or manufacturing partnerships, The Wall Street Journal reported Thursday.  Any deal there would come on the heels of Japan’s SoftBank making a $2 billion investment in Intel and Nvidia making its own $5 billion agreement to invest in Intel.

headline: TSMC, chip design software firms tap AI to help chips use less energy
summary: SANTA CLARA, California - (Reuters) -The computing chips that power artificial intelligence consume a lot of electricity.  On Wednesday, the world's biggest manufacturer of those chips showed off a new strategy to make them more energy efficient: Using AI-powered software to design them.  At a conference in Silicon Valley, Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co, the contract manufacturer that fabricates chips for Nvidia, showed off a range of ways that it is hoping to boost the energy efficiency of AI computing chips by about 10 times.
